<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Bonus Army March of 1932 consisted of:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Civil rights activists demanding equality</option>
            <option letter="b">WWI veterans demanding early payment of service bonuses</option>
            <option letter="c">Labor unions seeking higher wages</option>
            <option letter="d">Farmers protesting low crop prices</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Bonus Army was a group of World War I veterans who marched to Washington D.C. demanding early payment of their service certificates (bonuses), scheduled for 1945. When Hoover ordered the army to evict them, the violent removal of veterans and their families by troops under General MacArthur further damaged Hoover's public image during the Depression.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
